{"_id":"6yv9I5roVDUa1uMV","name":"PGR_Gourd Limpets","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/ship.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<h1>Boarding, Escort</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 3-0, Tenacity 10</strong></p>\n<p>These limpet pods can only be used to perform the <strong>PGR_Gourd Command</strong> tactic.</p>","lid":"ms_MlM53CfPX4mqePdYsWhwp","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":2,"name":"PGR_Gourd Limpets","source":null,"tags":[{"val":"10","tag":{"id":"hQUWmHtgOaF05Wfk","fallback_lid":"tg_JQGuxAyQxFGpfJRQFvwoQ","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"GsPrdH4DG2a0xrTW","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"JwqNMHKcDL3Cxz3G","fallback_lid":"tg_ena4nNzrrSQIF4jvacv6L","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}}],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_7MIEXmCi5X0FZ4JO75hQD","name":"PGR_Gourd Command (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Tactic</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 3-0</strong></p>\n<p>You deploy PGR_Gourd Limpets toward a hostile <strong>Capital Ship</strong> as a boarding action. During the <strong>Boarding Phase</strong>, these limpets disgorge their contents into the ship and you give them one of the following commands:<br /><br />&bull; <strong>CONSUME</strong>: Apply <strong>3 Greywash Counters</strong> to the boarded ship on a successful boarding roll, or <strong>1 Greywash Counter on a failure</strong>. Spending a maneuver to clear Greywash Counters also repels this unit as well. This boarding action can stack with itself. <br />&bull; <strong>SURGE (Limited 1)</strong>: Double the number of <strong>Greywash Counters</strong> on the boarded ship. If this boarding action fails, you do not expend this command&rsquo;s <strong>LIMITED</strong> use.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>PGR_Gourd limpets are terribly cruel nanite weapons, likely created and propagated by HORUS cells. After attaching to an enemy vessel, the limpets disgorge liters of &ldquo;greywash&rdquo; into their targets. These nanite washes tear through the open spaces inside of capital ships, consuming organic and soft inorganic material, eliminating the enemy without firing a shot. All that is left after a greywash burnout is a brownish-red slurry of processed waste material, empty hardsuits, and dead nanites.</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GjHC5MEByTSnx251"}}}
{"_id":"9MzTwqzqpjpz2Pdh","name":"Bomber Wing","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/drone.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>Gain the Bomber Command and Active Countermeasures tactics.</p>","lid":"ms_JzENvCsmxudiKEHJ-LtG3","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":2,"name":"Bomber Wing","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"GsPrdH4DG2a0xrTW","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_uhvBVw-YT885OJt9cgYaD","name":"Bomber Command (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Tactic</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 2-0</strong></p>\n<p>Choose one <strong>BOMBER WING</strong> assigned to your battlegroup and give it the following command:<br /><br />&bull; <strong>Torpedoes Away</strong>: Deal <strong>4 damage</strong> to a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong>. You may assign another unused <strong>BOMBER WING</strong> from your battlegroup to assist, dealing an additional <strong>+2 damage</strong>.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""},{"lid":"act_uwYRhGOt9rSk-qcMrFSeZ","name":"Active Countermeasures (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Tactic</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 4-0</strong></p>\n<p>Choose one <strong>BOMBER WING</strong> assigned to your battlegroup and give it the following command:<br /><br />&bull; <strong>Deploy Chaff (Limited 1)</strong>: Choose a <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong> in your battlegroup or an allied battlegroup in the same range band. Until the end of your next turn, the next time that ship takes damage reduce it by <strong>1d3</strong>. This effect does not stack.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Bombers are larger vessels crewed by two to four crewmembers and loaded with anti- capital ordnance that lets them punch far above their weight class. If ignored, a wing of these ships can be as dangerous as a single ship of the line. Bombers are also frequently outfitted with large reserves of defensive countermeasures to help screen their carrier&rsquo;s advance and during strike operations, including pulse-flares, EMP charges, and decoy signal emitters.</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"DSczL9A1ETX81W7z","name":"Payload Outrider Escort","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/ship.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>This special<strong> ESCORT</strong> accompanies launched munitions, clearing the way for them to safely and accurately strike their targets. When you or an allied battlegroup in the same range band makes a <strong>PAYLOAD</strong> attack, you may assign this squadron to accompany that attack. If more than one <strong>PAYLOAD</strong> attack is fired at a time, choose one to accompany. Each <strong>PAYLOAD</strong> attack can only be accompanied by a single <strong>PAYLOAD OUTRIDER ESCORT</strong>.<br /><br />An accompanied <strong>PAYLOAD</strong> attack cannot have <strong>Flight Counters</strong> added to it from hostile effects or abilities. During the <strong>Impact Phase</strong>, add <strong>+1 damage</strong> to that attack for each <strong>Flight Counter</strong> removed from it before impact. You may also force the target battlegroup to reroll 1 Interdiction die of your choice and take the worst result; however, if this attack&rsquo;s damage is completely interdicted, then this <strong>ESCORT</strong> is destroyed as well.</p>","lid":"ms_MlM53CfPX4mqePdYsWhwp","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":2,"name":"Payload Outrider Escort","source":null,"tags":[],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Subline outriders are frequently tasked with escorting payloads across space, ensuring their uncontested delivery to the target. These units provide a mixture of physical point-defense coverage as well as immediate-response electronic protective measures and adaptive course corrections to both safeguard payloads in transit and help guarantee optimal impact, though this often places them in harm&rsquo;s way far from the protection of other ships in their fleet.</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GjHC5MEByTSnx251"}}}
{"_id":"GUUzLW1DZocnMTYZ","name":"PIPECLEANER Subalterns","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/ship.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<h1>Boarding, Escort</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 3-0, Tenacity 12</strong></p>\n<p>These fearsome combat subalterns can infiltrate and sabotage areas of a ship that would be hazardous or inaccessible for humans, such as the power storage systems for long-spool weapons. When this unit succeeds on <strong>Sabotage Fire Control</strong> against a ship with one or more <strong>CHARGE </strong>weapons, that ship must also choose one: add <strong>1 Charge Counter</strong> to a <strong>Charge</strong> weapon of your choice or take <strong>5 damage</strong>. A boarded ship can only suffer from this effect 1/round.<br /><br />Whenever a boarded ship fails a roll to repel this unit, the ship takes <strong>2 damage</strong>.</p>","lid":"ms_MlM53CfPX4mqePdYsWhwp","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":2,"name":"PIPECLEANER Subalterns","source":null,"tags":[{"val":"12","tag":{"id":"hQUWmHtgOaF05Wfk","fallback_lid":"tg_JQGuxAyQxFGpfJRQFvwoQ","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"JwqNMHKcDL3Cxz3G","fallback_lid":"tg_ena4nNzrrSQIF4jvacv6L","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}}],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>PIPECLEANER subalterns, part of IPS-N&rsquo;s Warfighter line, are commonly inserted into enemy ships at dangerous, unconventional breach-points. They can be remotely controlled by a human handler but are more often commanded by a projected NHP partition controlling a networked squad as a single unit. Humanoid in appearance, they are built with many more points of articulation along with secondary bladed appendages for activity in close, low or null-g environments. In combat, they act with frightening, uncanny speed and movements</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GjHC5MEByTSnx251"}}}
{"_id":"GjHC5MEByTSnx251","name":"Marine Landers","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/ship.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<h1>Boarding, Escort</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 3-0, Tenacity 10</strong></p>","lid":"ms_MlM53CfPX4mqePdYsWhwp","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":0,"name":"Marine Landers","source":null,"tags":[{"val":"10","tag":{"id":"hQUWmHtgOaF05Wfk","fallback_lid":"tg_JQGuxAyQxFGpfJRQFvwoQ","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"JwqNMHKcDL3Cxz3G","fallback_lid":"tg_ena4nNzrrSQIF4jvacv6L","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}}],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>The design of marine boarding vessels has changed little in the last 100 years of naval warfare. Minimally armed and moderately armored, built for speed and carrying capacity, these craft are solely designed to make contact with enemy ships and breach their outer hulls to allow their passengers to begin the perilous task of boarding actions. Veteran marines have a wealth of colorful nicknames for these ships, few of which are fit for polite company.</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GjHC5MEByTSnx251"}}}
{"_id":"NvPUuP6a7JEe5Hfv","name":"Balor Chassis Wing","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/drone.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p><strong>Boarding, Tenacity 12, Greywash, Unique</strong></p>\n<p>The Balor&rsquo;s nanoswarm construction allows it to hellishly regenerate physical damage sustained during combat. During the<strong> Logistics Phase</strong>, this unit repairs <strong>2 HP</strong>.<br /><br />Additionally, gain the <strong>Balor Command</strong> tactic.</p>","lid":"ms_JzENvCsmxudiKEHJ-LtG3","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":3,"name":"Balor Chassis Wing","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"JwqNMHKcDL3Cxz3G","fallback_lid":"tg_ena4nNzrrSQIF4jvacv6L","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}},{"val":"12","tag":{"id":"hQUWmHtgOaF05Wfk","fallback_lid":"tg_JQGuxAyQxFGpfJRQFvwoQ","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_uhvBVw-YT885OJt9cgYaD","name":"Balor Command (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Tactic</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 3-0</strong></p>\n<p>Give the <strong>BALOR CHASSIS WING</strong> one of these commands:<br /><br />&bull; <strong>Nanocomposite Munitions:</strong> Deal <strong>2 damage</strong> to a hostile <strong>ESCORT</strong> or <strong>WING</strong>, or consume <strong>LOCK ON</strong> from a <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong> to deal <strong>2 damage</strong> to that ship, give it <strong>2 Greywash Counters</strong>, and take <strong>2 damage</strong> in return. <br />&bull; <strong>Hive Frenzy: </strong>Assign this unit to board a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong>. Each time it succeeds on a boarding roll, the boarded ship gains <strong>2 Greywash Counters</strong>. Ships do not remove Greywash Counters during the <strong>Impact Phase</strong> while this <strong>Wing</strong> is aboard them.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>One of the more infamous HORUS pattern- groups, the Balor is a highly resilient chassis that employs frame-integrated, neurosynced &ldquo;hellswarms&rdquo; of greywash nanites in both offensive and defensive capacities. First encountered during the latter days of the Sanjak Rebellion under the command of the Maw, a Baronic Free Company turned decentralized hive-being, the Balor enjoys a grim reputation as persistent and intractable danger within Baronic space and beyond, but some ambitious Karrakin commanders in the Dawnline Shore have developed an appreciation for the unique tactical advantages they offer as horrifyingly effective boarding units.</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"VguFjoOU6FU5NubR","name":"Tortuga Chassis Wing","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/drone.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p><strong>Boarding, Tenacity 12, Unique</strong></p>\n<p>Gain the <strong>Tortuga Command</strong> tactic</p>","lid":"ms_JzENvCsmxudiKEHJ-LtG3","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":3,"name":"Tortuga Chassis Wing","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"JwqNMHKcDL3Cxz3G","fallback_lid":"tg_ena4nNzrrSQIF4jvacv6L","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}},{"val":"12","tag":{"id":"hQUWmHtgOaF05Wfk","fallback_lid":"tg_JQGuxAyQxFGpfJRQFvwoQ","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_uhvBVw-YT885OJt9cgYaD","name":"Tortuga Command (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Tactic</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 3-0</strong></p>\n<p>Give the <strong>TORTUGA CHASSIS WING</strong> one of the following commands:<br /><br />&bull; <strong>Heavy Gunner: </strong>Deal <strong>1d3 damage</strong> to a hostile <strong>ESCORT</strong> or <strong>WING</strong>. Until the end of your next turn, the next time the <strong>TORTUGA CHASSIS WING</strong> or the ship it is equipped to takes damage from an <strong>ESCORT</strong> or <strong>WING</strong> while within<strong> Range 3&ndash;0</strong>, you may deal <strong>3 damage </strong>to it in response. <br />&bull; <strong>Decksweepers: </strong>Repel a boarding unit from a ship in your battlegroup or in an allied battlegroup in the same range band, then deal <strong>3 damage</strong> to that unit. <br />&bull; <strong>Daisy Cutters: </strong>Assign this unit to board a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP.</strong> Each time it succeeds on a boarding roll, the boarded ship takes <strong>2 damage</strong>. 2/engagement, you may increase this to <strong>1d6+1 damage</strong> instead.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>IPS-N&rsquo;s Tortuga is one of the corpro&rsquo;s most iconic and widespread chassis designs, offered in whole-fleet line contracts to numerous clients and states. The Tortuga is purpose-built to operate in deep space; though it makes for an adequate strike unit with the addition of a chassis mount, the Tortuga is primarily meant to breach and clear carrier decks, hostile station environments, and the spinal columns of capital ships. With its heavy, angular hull it serves as both battering ram and bulwark, clearing a path for allied boarders as it advances. An integrated WATCHDOG co-pilot system provides pilots with additional full-spectrum response capability under even heavy fire.</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"WQFWkUdiGtbsjnNX","name":"Legion Drone Nexus","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/drone.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>1/round, you may order a <strong>LEGION DRONE NEXUS</strong> in your battlegroup to interpose itself between friendly units and incoming fire. Reduce hostile damage dealt to an <strong>ESCORT</strong> or <strong>WING</strong> in your battlegroup or an allied battlegroup in the same range band by 1. This <strong>WING</strong> then takes <strong>2 damage</strong>. Additionally, gain the <strong>Legion Command</strong> tactic.</p>","lid":"ms_JzENvCsmxudiKEHJ-LtG3","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":0,"name":"Legion Drone Nexus","source":null,"tags":[],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_uhvBVw-YT885OJt9cgYaD","name":"Legion Command (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Tactic</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 3-0</strong></p>\n<p>Choose one<strong> LEGION DRONE NEXUS</strong> assigned to your battlegroup and give it the following command. As part of this, you may assign another unused <strong>LEGION DRONE NEXUS</strong> from your battlegroup to join the sortie, giving them the same command. Allied battlegroups in your range band may use this tactic to command your <strong>LEGION DRONE NEXUSES</strong> as if they were under their control:<br /><br />&bull; <strong>Hunt/Kill</strong>: Deal <strong>1 damage </strong>to a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong>, <strong>ESCORT</strong>, or <strong>WING</strong>, or deal <strong>2 damage</strong> to a hostile <strong>ESCORT</strong> or <strong>WING</strong> and take <strong>2 damage</strong> in return.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Remotely piloted drone fighters controlled as appendages of a fleet legion are a simple and cost-effective method of force projection that also serves to minimize overall casualties during engagements. Despite this, susceptibility to electronic interference and systemic attacks prevents them from ever fully replacing manned strike craft. Fully integrated fleetwide tactical networking allows all battlegroup commanders to coordinate drone operations to and from any ship as necessary.</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"bVdYdAQkzeWnr0mY","name":"Minelayers","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/ship.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[{"lid":"tempLID","name":"Reloading","val":0,"max":2,"min":0}],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>This special <strong>ESCORT</strong> is tasked with deploying minefields. During the <strong>Logistics Phase</strong> you may order it to deploy minefields in the range band either directly ahead of you or directly behind you. Until the start of the next <strong>Logistics Phase</strong>, the first time a hostile battlegroup forces you or an allied battlegroup to move into or out of that range band, the mines detonate and the hostile battlegroup takes <strong>10 AREA- TARGET</strong> damage. Due to sheer saturation, this cannot be reduced below <strong>2 area damage</strong> by <strong>Interdiction</strong>. Minefields cannot stack with themselves.</p>","lid":"ms_MlM53CfPX4mqePdYsWhwp","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":2,"name":"Minelayers","source":null,"tags":[{"val":"2","tag":{"id":"4zljqurutuldbJiO","fallback_lid":"tg_8FBdSdkbLqsDsDmyJwlCa","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}}],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>The term &ldquo;mines&rdquo; is a bit of a misnomer in the context of naval combat operations. Rather than stationary defensive emplacements, naval mines are more akin to missiles, seeded in clouds across anticipated approach vectors to maximize the odds of terminal contact. Mines loiter in a low-power state until their sensors detect hostile vessels in proximity, at which point they activate and home in on the nearest target at full burn. Most naval vessels do not carry mines as part of their standard ordnance loadout, delegating minelaying duties to specialized subline vessels instead.</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GjHC5MEByTSnx251"}}}
{"_id":"cVSqjJ6rMlcc4Bd8","name":"Mounted Chassis Wing","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/drone.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p><strong>Boarding, Tenacity 11</strong></p>\n<p>Gain the <strong>Chassis Command</strong> tactic.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","lid":"ms_JzENvCsmxudiKEHJ-LtG3","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":2,"name":"Mounted Chassis Wing","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"JwqNMHKcDL3Cxz3G","fallback_lid":"tg_ena4nNzrrSQIF4jvacv6L","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}},{"val":"11","tag":{"id":"hQUWmHtgOaF05Wfk","fallback_lid":"tg_JQGuxAyQxFGpfJRQFvwoQ","type":"tag","reg_name":"game"}}],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_uhvBVw-YT885OJt9cgYaD","name":"Chassis Command (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Tactic</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 3-0</strong></p>\n<p>Choose a <strong>MOUNTED CHASSIS WING</strong> in your battlegroup and give it one of these commands:<br /><br />&bull; <strong>Toe-to-Toe: </strong>Deal <strong>1d3 damage</strong> to a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP, ESCORT, or WING.</strong> <br />&bull;<strong> Breach and Clear:</strong> Assign this unit to board a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP.</strong> Each time it succeeds on a boarding roll, the boarded ship takes <strong>2 damage.</strong></p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Chassis mounts are exterior-mounted frames that allow mechs them to operate in deep space. With a mount installed, mechs rocket toward enemy capital ships, dogfight, and maneuver in space with far more agility than conventional mech-tier EVA units would otherwise allow.</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"gJH227udRC2nKnyP","name":"Barbarossa Chassis Wing","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/drone.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>The integrated flak launchers and anti-aerospace munitions carried by this WING count as an AUXILIARY weapon for your battlegroup. When fired alongside any PRIMARY single-target weapon targeting a CAPITAL SHIP or ESCORT within Range 3&ndash;0, these weapons deal 1 damage to that same target and 3 damage to a hostile WING in the same battlegroup. Additionally, gain the Barbarossa Command tactic.</p>","lid":"ms_JzENvCsmxudiKEHJ-LtG3","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":3,"name":"Barbarossa Chassis Wing","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_uhvBVw-YT885OJt9cgYaD","name":"Barbarossa Command (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Tactic</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 3-0</strong></p>\n<p>Give the <strong>BARBAROSSA CHASSIS WING</strong> one of these commands:<br /><br />&bull; <strong>Siege Cannons</strong>: Deal <strong>3 damage</strong> to a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong> or <strong>ESCORT</strong>. <br />&bull; <strong>Charge Apocalypse Rails (Reloading 2)</strong>: This <strong>Wing</strong> begins charging its integrated Apocalypse Rail weapons. During the next <strong>Impact Phase</strong>, you may order it to open fire on a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong> or <strong>ESCORT </strong>within range. Make a single-target attack roll, dealing<strong> 2d6 </strong>damage on hit with <strong>OVERKILL</strong> and <strong>RELIABLE 4</strong>.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Harrison Armory&rsquo;s Barbarossa heavy siege chassis is an artillery/anti-air frame designed to engage targets in both terrestrial and low-gravity operations. Equipped with an integrated LGC-04 &ldquo;Apocalypse Rail&rdquo; gravitic catapult, the Barbarossa can capably engage subline vessels, and in massed volleys can even threaten capital ships. The additional power plants and stabilizers provided by a chassis mount help mitigate the drawbacks of the famously temperamental Apocalypse Rail, allowing for more consistent output while still permitting full zero-g maneuverability</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ii9gpoMziqMUXiL4","name":"Subline Pickets","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/ship.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>These special ships are tasked with scouting the battlefield, and have already taken up their position prior to the engagement. 1/round, you or an ally of your choice may add <strong>+1 ACCURACY</strong> to a single-target attack.</p>","lid":"ms_MlM53CfPX4mqePdYsWhwp","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":2,"name":"Subline Pickets","source":null,"tags":[],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Sleek, fast, and minimally armed, subline picket ships scout the predicted battlefield days before capital ships arrive, running silent and cold to avoid enemy sensors. Picket postings are lonely and seldom comfortable, operating on minimal power and under communications blackout protocols for extended durations, but once combat begins the data they feed captains on enemy positioning, numbers, direction, and trajectory can be crucial to a fleet&rsquo;s success.</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GjHC5MEByTSnx251"}}}
{"_id":"kdTLwcMrEgSsOdTn","name":"Destroyer Escort","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/ship.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>The pulse lances, kinetic guns, or missile batteries carried by this ESCORT count as an AUXILIARY weapon for your battlegroup. When fired alongside any PRIMARY single-target weapon targeting a CAPITAL SHIP or ESCORT within Range 3&ndash;0, these weapons deal 2 damage to that same target. Additionally, gain the Destroyer Command tactic.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","lid":"ms_fT1cDCxAsfMy6yjBbuhDk","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":2,"name":"Destroyer Escort","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"GsPrdH4DG2a0xrTW","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_BWT5oZb5vhDPbxb6qpjA9","name":"Destroyer Command (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Tactic</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 3-0</strong></p>\n<p>Choose one DESTROYER assigned to your battlegroup and give it one of the following commands:<br /><br />&bull; <strong>Cannonade</strong>: Deal <strong>3 damage</strong> to a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong>. <br />&bull; <strong>Snapflight Torpedoes</strong>: Deal <strong>6 damage</strong> to a hostile <strong>ESCORT</strong>. <br />&bull; <strong>Encirclement (Limited 1)</strong>: Advance or fall back one range band. You may not use this command if you have used an effect or ability to move this turn, and after using it you may not move again this turn.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Sleek, fast, and outfitted with powerful weapons sufficient to threaten both capital ships and other subline vessels alike, destroyer designs often sacrifice as many nonessential functions as possible to maximize their effective firepower. Destroyers typically operate in wolfpacks, prowling the perimeter of engagements on the lookout for opportunities to strike at a fleet&rsquo;s exposed flanks.</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"lCDzLTcUu5r6Bwuu","name":"Cruiser Escort","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/ship.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>When a hostile battlegroup forces your battlegroup or an allied battlegroup in the same range band to fall back or move forward any number of range bands, you may have this <strong>ESCORT</strong> deploy a field of seeker mines that deal <strong>4 damage</strong> to a <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong> or <strong>ESCORT </strong>of your choice in that battlegroup. You may use this ability 1/round for each <strong>CRUISER ESCORT</strong> in your battlegroup, but only once per instance of hostile movement. Additionally, gain the <strong>Cruiser Command</strong> tactic.</p>","lid":"ms_fT1cDCxAsfMy6yjBbuhDk","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":3,"name":"Cruiser Escort","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"GsPrdH4DG2a0xrTW","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_BWT5oZb5vhDPbxb6qpjA9","name":"Cruiser Command (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Tactic</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 3-0</strong></p>\n<p>Choose one CRUISER assigned to your battlegroup and give it one of the following commands:<br /><br />&bull; <strong>Fire at Will:</strong> Deal <strong>4 damage</strong> to a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong>. You may also deal<strong> 2 AREA-TARGET</strong> damage to all <strong>ESCORTS</strong> in that ship&rsquo;s battlegroup and take <strong>2 damage</strong> in return. This damage cannot be interdicted. <br />&bull; <strong>Defensive Gunnery: </strong>Gain <strong>+3 Interdiction</strong> until the start of your next turn. <br />&bull; <strong>Local Kill Screen (Limited 1):</strong> Deal<strong> 5 damage</strong> to a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong> or <strong>ESCORT</strong>, deal <strong>2 damage</strong> to all of that ship&rsquo;s <strong>WINGS</strong>, and that ship makes all single-target attacks with<strong> +1 DIFFICULTY</strong> until the end of its next turn.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>The largest subline ships, only a step below frigates, cruisers mount a wide array of offensive and defensive systems that allow them to flexibly and robustly reinforce a fleet&rsquo;s threat envelope as circumstances dictate. Relatively independent for subline vessels and often used for in-system patrols or local planetary defense, the command of a cruiser is often seen as a vital step in a naval officer&rsquo;s career.</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"lLTRj2DLobF7AxkU","name":"Corvette Escort","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/ship.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>Designating targets for close fire support allows these escorts to rapidly track and engage them. 1/round when you LOCK ON to a ship within Range 3&ndash;0 you may deal 1 damage to it for each of these ESCORTS in your battlegroup, to a maximum of 4 damage. Additionally, gain the Corvette Command tactic:</p>","lid":"ms_fT1cDCxAsfMy6yjBbuhDk","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":1,"name":"Corvette Escort","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"GsPrdH4DG2a0xrTW","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_BWT5oZb5vhDPbxb6qpjA9","name":"Corvette Command (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Tactic</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 3-0</strong></p>\n<p>Choose one <strong>CORVETTE ESCORT</strong> assigned to your battlegroup and give it one of these commands:<br /><br />&bull; <strong>Trade Blows</strong>: Deal <strong>2 damage</strong> to a hostile Wing, or deal <strong>4 damage </strong>to a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong> and take <strong>2 damage</strong> in return. <br />&bull; <strong>Defensive Formation</strong>: Gain <strong>+2 Interdiction</strong> until the start of your next turn. <br />&bull; <strong>Gun Run (Limited 1)</strong>: Deal <strong>2 AREA-TARGET</strong> damage to a hostile battlegroup. Consuming <strong>LOCK ON</strong> from <strong>CAPITAL SHIPS</strong> or <strong>ESCORTS</strong> in that battlegroup increases this to <strong>4 damage</strong> against those specific ships. This damage cannot be interdicted.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Corvettes operate in small squadrons, fulfilling lighter-than/heavier-than duties that some fleet commanders prefer for versatility. The smallest subline vessels in use, corvettes are often tasked with fire support and targeted strike operations in a gunship-equivalent role.</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"v97EAeLxv1Tk7kzL","name":"Fighter Wing","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/drone.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>Gain <strong>+1 Interdiction</strong> for each <strong>FIGHTER WING</strong> as they maintain combat patrols within your fleet&rsquo;s perimeter, up to a maximum of <strong>+4 Interdiction</strong>. Additionally, gain the <strong>Fighter Command</strong> tactic</p>","lid":"ms_JzENvCsmxudiKEHJ-LtG3","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":1,"name":"Fighter Wing","source":null,"tags":[],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_uhvBVw-YT885OJt9cgYaD","name":"Fighter Command (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Tactic</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 2-0</strong></p>\n<p>Choose one <strong>Fighter Wing</strong> assigned to your battlegroup and give it one of the following commands. As part of this, you may assign another unused <strong>Fighter Wing</strong> from your battlegroup to join the sortie, selecting the same or a different command:<br /><br />&bull; <strong>Strafing Run</strong>: Deal <strong>1 damage</strong> to a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong> or <strong>ESCORT</strong>. <br />&bull;<strong> Engage and Eliminate: </strong>Deal <strong>3 damage</strong> to a hostile<strong> WING</strong>.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Fighters are small, multi-purpose, single- pilot ships with a wide combat portfolio, ranging from combat patrols, to subline escort, to ordnance interception. Fighter wings, though outclassed by the raw power of larger ships, are integral units in any battlegroup for their versatility alone.</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"xLjyb0vC6CrkG53j","name":"Monarch Chassis Wing","type":"mech_system","img":"systems/lancer/assets/icons/drone.svg","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"<p>The integrated SSC-30 High-Penetration Missile Systems carried by these mechs allow them to coordinate reactive volleys of Avenger micromissiles with other strikes. 1/round whenever a weapon in your battlegroup or an allied battlegroup in the same range band critically hits a target within Range 3&ndash;0, even if it doesn&rsquo;t have the CRITICAL tag, you may use these micromissiles to deal 2 damage to a hostile CAPITAL SHIP, ESCORT, or WING. Additionally, gain the Monarch Command tactic.</p>","lid":"ms_JzENvCsmxudiKEHJ-LtG3","integrated":[],"license":"","license_level":3,"name":"Monarch Chassis Wing","source":null,"tags":[{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"060yGC97tWUriLGk","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"comp_core"}}],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_uhvBVw-YT885OJt9cgYaD","name":"Monarch Command (Tactic)","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"<h1>Tactic</h1>\n<p><strong>Range 3-0</strong></p>\n<p>Give the MONARCH CHASSIS WING one of the following commands:<br /><br />&bull; <strong>Seeking Payloads:</strong> Deal <strong>2 damage</strong> to a hostile <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong> or <strong>ESCORT</strong>, or consume <strong>LOCK ON</strong> from a <strong>CAPITAL SHIP</strong> or <strong>ESCORT</strong> to deal <strong>4 damage</strong> to that ship and either deal <strong>2 damage</strong> to all of its <strong>WINGS</strong> or remove <strong>1 Flight Counter</strong> from one of your active <strong>PAYLOAD</strong> attacks. <br />&bull; <strong>Gandiva Missiles:</strong> This <strong>Wing</strong> launches a salvo of advanced Gandiva missiles. This is a <strong>PRIMARY</strong> single-target <strong>PAYLOAD</strong> attack that deals <strong>1d6+3</strong> damage and can be fired at up to two targets at a time, tracked individually. When using this command, you may consume <strong>LOCK ON</strong> from the target to add or remove one <strong>Flight Counter</strong> from that <strong>PAYLOAD</strong>.</p>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":true,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<p>Smith-Shimano&rsquo;s Monarch is a highly versatile all-theater combat chassis, part of the company&rsquo;s BELLA CIAO line, created to serve as a multirole missile launch platform. Rigorously designed to exacting standards and surprisingly agile for its size, Monarchs are equipped with advanced targeting systems capable of coordinating multiple simultaneous weapon launches for optimal effect. Though not originally intended as a naval combat chassis, the Monarch&rsquo;s responsive controls and ability to equip a wide variety of missile payloads have led to its increasing adoption by pilots who value its combination of speed and firepower.</p>","type":"Drone"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"HHrm6UaHtCrg3Wzn":3},"flags":{}}
